&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to coordinate multiple activities and ensure safety, quality, and schedule adherence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two years’ experience in Operations or a Solar and Wind Field Technician Role is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to demonstrate competent technical knowledge of plant and system processes and ex

&lt;h2 class=&quot;lumesse-section-header lumesse-section-header-0 jdesc-section-header&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 32, 96);&quot;&gt;What The Role Is&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports to the Manager, Control Center Operations, and will be located in our Scottsdale, AZ office. The Operations Analyst is instrumental in ensuring that our functions, indications, and processes around control system performance at our renewable energy facilities are best in class.&amp;nbsp; Operating out of the Clearway Renewable Performance Monitoring Center, the Remote Operations team monitors and controls ~10 GW of utility-scale renewable energy and BESS facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;lumesse-section-header lumesse-section-header-1 jdesc-section-header&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 32, 96);&quot;&gt;What You&#39;ll Be Doing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Real-Time Monitoring: Closely monitor facility voltage and real power controls for BESS, PV, and Wind assets, ensuring all systems function within prescribed operational parameters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dispatch Error Tracking: Continuously review unit control system data to identify, flag, and correct dispatch errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshooting &amp;amp; Issue Resolution: Rapidly respond to operational anomalies and control system issues, leveraging a deep understanding of unit controls to implement corrective measures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help determine critical monitoring points for control system design and change management to allow operators to quickly identify control system malfunctions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with SCADA/Controls Engineering and Operations IT to investigate, troubleshoot, and resolve unit errors. Collaborate with IT to design, develop, and refine real-time alarm systems associated with voltage and power controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the development and enhancement of alarms for control systems, ensuring robust notification and escalation pathways for operational variances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documentation: Author and maintain detailed control procedures, ensuring clear, accurate, and up-to-date records for all facility control operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aid in training support through the creation and revision of training materials for Operations Specialists, sharing expertise and best practices in real-time controls and dispatch operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply working knowledge of CAISO, PJM, and ERCOT, NERC, etc. requirements to ensure all monitored facilities meet regulatory and operational standards for energy and ancillary services dispatch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and perform control system testing for new projects and engineering design changes on existing projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
